Build and manage OCI container images for Frappe apps.

Commands for building production-ready container images that can be
deployed to any container runtime (Docker, Podman, Kubernetes).

Examples:
  weg image build              # Build image for current project
  weg image build --push       # Build and push to registry
  weg image list               # List local images
  weg image push <tag>         # Push image to registry

Usage:
  weg image [command]

Available Commands:
  build       Build a container image
  list        List container images
  push        Push an image to a registry

Flags:
  -h, --help   help for image

Global Flags:
  -C, --chdir string              Run as if weg was started in <path>
      --config string             Path to config file (default: auto-detect)
      --debug-categories string   Filter debug output: all,config,state,net,git,fs,exec
      --log-level string          Set log level: quiet, normal, verbose, debug, trace
  -o, --output string             Output format: auto, json, table, plain, quiet (default "auto")
  -q, --quiet                     Suppress non-essential output
  -v, --verbose count             Increase verbosity (-v, -vv, -vvv)
  -y, --yes                       Assume yes for all prompts

Use "weg image [command] --help" for more information about a command.
